div.div: The ALU reads in an instruction, and checks the first 3 bits.
If the first 3 bits correspond to the ADD or XOR instruction,
then the ALU will either add A and B together, or XOR them.
If an instruction is unrecognized, then the ALU will return

off and on, at each different state.
Contains additional blocks of hardware inside of it:
interpret_instruction -> Takes an instruction, and splits it into 3 different outputs:
next_state -> Takes the current FSM state, and outputs the next one
four_bit register -> Stores the FSM state value
